						               													<description>In Mahan's Wake is ATG&amp;rsquo;s third supplement for Dawn of the Battleship. It has thirty-one scenarios, a mix of historical battles, like the Sino-Japanese War, near-historical (&amp;ldquo;almost happened&amp;rdquo;), and fictional scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The latter include a series of scenarios called the Great Maritime War of 1899, by William Le Queux, one of the many &amp;ldquo;war scare&amp;rdquo; books of that period (the techno-thrillers of that age). The story line was converted into playable scenarios by the knowledgeable Bob Eldridge, who unfortunately passed away in 2017. Mike Harris, his co-author, has finished the work.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition to the scenarios, the book includes annexes covering all the ships and weapons required to play them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
